\" width=\"350\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7a/Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Maegor_Towers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/525px-Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Maegor_Towers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7a/Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Maegor_Towers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/700px-Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Maegor_Towers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Rhaena Targaryen and Maegor Towers by coldraindropsss ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"House Towers of Harrenhal\">House Towers</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/44_AC\" title=\"44 AC\">44&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/61_AC\" title=\"61 AC\">61&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Jordan_Towers\" title=\"Jordan Towers\">Jordan Towers</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Maegor Towers</b> was the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Towers_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"House Towers of Harrenhal\">House Towers</a> during the early reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Named_after\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Named after\">Named after</a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>, he was the last of his line.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character\">Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maegor_Towers&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Maegor was a sickly and impoverished young lord.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maegor_Towers&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Born in <a href=\"/index.php/44_AC\" title=\"44 AC\">44&#160;AC</a> to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jordan_Towers\" title=\"Jordan Towers\">Jordan Towers</a>, Maegor was <a href=\"/index.php/Named_after\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Named after\">named after</a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> who had granted his grandsire, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Walton_Towers\" title=\"Walton Towers\">Walton Towers</a>, the lordship of <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> that same year. Lord Jordan was a staunch supporter of the king and one of the last <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> who remained loyal to Maegor when the great lords of the realm flocked to Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Lord Jordan was one of the few lords that remained at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> to turn it over to Jaehaerys,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and he was pardoned in exchange for certain holdings and for sending the young Maegor to court to serve as a <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostage</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>As his elder brothers died in King Maegor's wars, the young Maegor became <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a> after his father passed away from a chest congestion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> When King Jaehaerys began a <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_progress\" title=\"Royal progress\">royal progress</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_53_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">53&#160;AC</a> with his <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a> to celebrate the new year, his first stop was to see the new Lord of Harrenhal, then only nine years of age.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In a castle built to house thousands, Maegor was an impoverished lord who resided in the <a href=\"/index.php/Tower_of_Dread\" title=\"Tower of Dread\">Tower of Dread</a> with only a cook and three elderly <a href=\"/index.php/Men-at-arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Men-at-arms\">men-at-arms</a>. Since the rest of Harrenhal was empty, King Jaehaerys settled his widowed sister, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>, in the <a href=\"/index.php/Widow%27s_Tower\" title=\"Widow&#39;s Tower\">Widow's Tower</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/56_AC\" title=\"56 AC\">56&#160;AC</a>. Maegor and Rhaena eventually became friends, and she cared for his servants after Maegor passed away in <a href=\"/index.php/61_AC\" title=\"61 AC\">61&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> As Maegor was last of his line with no heirs,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Harrenhal was granted to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Strong\" title=\"House Strong\">House Strong</a> after Rhaena passed away in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_73_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">73&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maegor_Towers&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Walton_Towers\" title=\"Walton Towers\">Walton</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />wife</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\